# Core Engineering Rules

- Prefer simple, proven implementations over clever abstractions.
- Keep changes small and scoped; avoid touching unrelated code.
- For new behavior, define acceptance checks before coding.
- Make architecture decisions explicit in docs when trade-offs exist.
- Avoid premature optimization; profile before deep optimization work.

# Quality Gates

- No silent failures: log context and return explicit errors.
- No magic numbers in gameplay logic; move to config.
- No dead code, commented-out blocks, or placeholder TODO chains.
- Preserve backward compatibility for save/config formats when possible.

# Example

```csharp
// BAD
if (hp <= 0) state = 3;

// GOOD
if (hp <= 0) state = EntityState.Dead;
```
